column2: The protagonist of "28 Weeks Later" is Don Harris, portrayed by Robert Carlyle. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/28_Weeks_Later?utm_source=openai))
Bill S. Preston, Esq. and Ted "Theodore" Logan

The protagonist of the 2011 film "Drive" is known as "The Driver," portrayed by Ryan Gosling. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drive_%282011_film%29?utm_source=openai))
Nick Hendricks, Dale Arbus, Kurt Buckman
The protagonist of "Purple Rain" is The Kid, portrayed by Prince. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Purple_Rain_%28film%29?utm_source=openai))
Chief Inspector Lee and Detective James Carter

The film "Sex, Lies, and Videotape" features four main characters: Ann Bishop Mullany, John Mullany, Cynthia Patrice Bishop, and Graham Dalton. Due to the film's ensemble cast and the interwoven nature of their stories, it does not have a single clear protagonist. ([criterion.com](https://www.criterion.com/current/posts/962-sex-lies-and-videotape?utm_source=openai))

The protagonist of "The Postman" (1997) is an unnamed drifter who adopts the role of a postman in a post-apocalyptic America. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Postman_%28film%29?utm_source=openai))
The protagonist of "The Time Machine" is the Time Traveller. ([gradesaver.com](https://www.gradesaver.com/the-time-machine/study-guide/character-list/?utm_source=openai))
The protagonist of the 2013 film "Under the Skin" is portrayed by Scarlett Johansson. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Under_the_Skin_%282013_film%29?utm_source=openai))
